article.headline: South Florida 68, Southern Miss 60
article.story: TAMPA, Fla. (AP) -- Bradley Mosley scored a season-high 30 points to help South Florida earn its first Conference USA win of the season, 68-60 over Southern Miss on Friday night. Mosley, who played all 40 minutes for the seventh time this season, made 10-of-22 shots from the field and 7-of-12 from the foul line for the Bulls (7-14, 1-9), who won for the first time since Dec. 30 -- a span of 10 games. Gerrick Morris narrowly missed a triple-double, finishing with eight points, nine blocked shots and 10 rebounds for the winners. Brian Swift had 13 points and a game-high eight assists for South Florida, which held on despite using only seven players. Charles Gaines had 20 points and 12 rebounds for Southern Miss (11-10, 4-6), which lost for the fourth time in its last six games. Jasper Johnson came off the bench to score 13 points and grab 10 rebounds for the Golden Eagles, but he shot just 4-of-15 from the field. Southern Miss shot only 35.5 percent in the second half, while allowing South Florida to connect on 55 percent of its shots after halftime. Greg Johnson added 11 points for Southern Miss, which held a 26-7 edge in bench scoring and a 40-33 rebounding advantage.
